<!--
  Robust MISMO 3.6 sample loan application used by the Rule Service integration tests.

  This document is intentionally richer than sample-loan-application.xml so the
  ComprehensiveMortgageRules library can exercise the full range of formula methods
  and comparison rules:
	* Two borrowers (primary + co-borrower) to test indexed/aggregate borrower rules.
	* Multiple assets and liabilities to test collection counts and sums.
	* Fully populated loan terms, transaction detail, and subject property.
	* String fields (names, city, state) to test LEFT/RIGHT/UPPER/LOWER/TRIM/CONCAT.
	* Numeric fields (amounts, rates, counts) to test MIN/MAX/ROUND/ABS/SUM/INT.

  NOTE: Hydration is performed by Mortgage.Model.Translators.MISMO.MortgageFileMismoTranslator.
  Only the elements that the translator maps are guaranteed to populate the domain model;
  see ComprehensiveMortgageRules.json for the rules authored against the hydrated fields.
-->
